==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, {{term|ablucioun||cleansing of impurities|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|ablution|lang=fro}}, and its source, {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|ablūtiō||a washing away}}, from {{m|la|abluō||wash away}}, from {{term|ab||away|lang=la}} + {{m|la|luō||wash}}<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=3}}</ref>.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbluː.ʃn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈblu.ʃn̩/|/æbˈlu.ʃn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|uːʃən|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-ablution.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of washing something.
## {{context|chemistry|lang=en}} Originally, the [[purifying]] of oils and other substances by emulsification with hot water; now more generally, a thorough [[cleansing]] of a [[precipitate]] or other non-dissolved substance. {{defdate|First attested from around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
## The act of [[washing]] or [[cleansing]] the body, or some part of it, as a [[religious]] [[rite]]. {{defdate|From mid 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=5-6}}</ref>
## {{context|literary|or|humorous|usually|in the plural|lang=en}} [[washing|Washing]] oneself; [[bathing]], cleaning oneself up. {{defdate|From mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
##* {{quote-book|year=1835|author=[[s:Author:William Gilmore Simms|William Gilmore Simms]]|title=[[s:The Partisan|The Partisan]]|publisher=Harper|section=[[s:The Partisan/II|Chapter II]]|page=[[s:Page:The Partisan, v1.djvu/26|25]]|passage=He followed the steps of Bella, who soon conducted him to his chamber, and left him to those '''ablutions''' which a long ride along a sandy road had rendered particularly necessary.}}
## {{context|Western|_|Christianity|lang=en}} The [[rinse|rinsing]] of the priest's hand and the sacred vessel following the [[Communion]] with, depending on [[rite]], [[water]] or a mix of it and [[wine]], which may then be drunk by the priest. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
# The liquid used in the cleansing or ablution. {{defdate|From early 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* [[w:Alexander Pope|Alexander Pope]]
#*: Cast the '''ablutions''' in the main.
# {{context|Orthodox|_|Christianity|lang=en}} The [[ritual]] consumption by the [[deacon]] or priest of [[leftover]] sacred wine of host after the Communion.
# {{context|pluralonly|UK|military|lang=en}} The location or building where the showers and sinks are located. {{defdate|From mid 20<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

